I do not want to focus on who is to blame for the periodically recurring massacres and who is the victim. After all, today's citizens of Israel, including the autonomous territories, were born into the current political situation and did not live through the beginnings of the violence.
My intention is to offer readers a peek behind the curtain, a look to discover who is profiting from the tensions that have been dragging on for 95 years (calculated from the Balfour Declaration in November 1917) on a small area of land in the Middle East.
Some of my considerations are based on historical facts, others on conclusions I have reached on the basis of my own understanding of who or what group of people is the prime mover in the events of modern history.
In the history of mankind, the history of power struggles is at the forefront.
